                                                                           Module 5-Frontend-HTML5

Theory Assignment

	•	Question 1:difference between html & html 5?
	⁃	HTML does not provide native audio and video support.html only supports vector graphics if used in conjunction with different technologies like flash, VML ,or Silverlight.
	⁃	HTML5 provides native audio and video support.html5 supports SVG (Scalable Vector Graphics),Canvas,and other virtual vector graphics.



	•	Question 2:What are the additional tags used in HtML5?
	⁃	 HTML5 tags  <header> <nav> <aside> <article> <section> <footer> 

Lab Assignment(Task)
Create a audio video tag
Also applied properties like muted loop autoplay
Create some shape using canvas tag in html
Create some shape using svg tag in html

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>hello video audio svg tag canvas tag</h1>
        <video height="250px" muted loop autoplay src="/Gangster New Orleans gameplay part-1 - Aadi plays (720p, h264).mp4"></video>
        
        <audio controls  muted autoplay src="/Gangster New Orleans gameplay part-1.mp3"></audio> 
  
         
        <svg   fill="skyblue">
          <circle cx="150" cy="35" r="25" />

          <Rect x="10" y="10" width="100" height="50" fill="red"/>
      </svg>

      

        <canvas id="canavs"></canvas>
    <script>
       var cnv = document.getElementById("canavs")
       console.log(cnv)
       var cnt = cnv.getContext('2d') 
        cnt.fillStyle = 'blue';
        cnt.fillRect(10, 10, 100, 50);
        console.log(cnv);
   </script>

